# Technical Features/Concepts used in BMS

1. Used Interface projection (MoviesShowResponseProjection) and constructor projection.
2. Used native query in MoviesRepository interface
3. Global Exception Handler
4. Enums with custom code names - Need to handle for DB Insertion
5. Created ContextMapper interface for generic mapper.
6. Implemented interface projection for findMoviesByLanguage in movies repo and services layer.
7. Avoided @autowired field annotation and used construtor injection.
8. Understand usage of sealed interface.
9. CacaseType.ALL and other cascade usage

JPA information:
-----------------
Rules:
-------
1. When you are updating or inserting parent row, child row needs to be inserted first and then only parent row should be inserted. else you will be getting below error:

Exception -->org.hibernate.TransientPropertyValueException: Persistent instance of 'com.scaler.bms.entity.ShowSeat'
references an unsaved transient instance of 'com.scaler.bms.entity.ShowSeatLock' (persist the transient instance before flushing)
[com.scaler.bms.entity.ShowSeat.showSeatLock -> com.scaler.bms.entity.ShowSeatLock]

To have 2 approaches to avoid this:

1. First save the child and then parent entity using "SAVE" method.
2. Use @Transactional annotation, fetch the details by Id and just use .set<FieldName>.
Now hibernate will automatically do it. Also apply CASCADE.ALL in the entity.

Without @Transactional if we try to fetch by id and set the value, it won't be updated in DB table.